<p><b>Donald "Don" McLean</b> (born October 2, 1945) is an American singer-songwriter. He is most famous for the 1971 album <i><a href="American_Pie_(album)" title="American Pie (album)">American Pie</a></i>, containing the songs "<a href="American_Pie_(song)" title="American Pie (song)">American Pie</a>" and "<a href="Vincent_(song)" title="Vincent (song)">Vincent</a>".</p>
